# Task 2: D-06 LLM Failure Handling - 3-Retry Ceiling and Final Failure Reporting

## Transport: PinchTab (port 9867, normal server mode)
## Frontend: http://localhost:3000
## Backend: http://localhost:3001

## Failure Induction Method
Changed GLM provider API key to "invalid-key-for-testing" via POST /api/settings.
This causes real LLM connection failures when the generator role attempts suggest-seeds calls.

## Retry Ledger

### Attempt 1/3
- Action: Continue to DNA (suggest-seeds call)
- Result: FAILED in ~3 seconds
- Visible UI: Navigated to /campaign/new/dna with 6 empty DNA textareas
- Error surface: toast.error("Failed to generate suggestions") shown briefly
- Backend error: LLM API returns authentication error for invalid key
- Recovery state: UI shows validation "Add at least one enabled DNA seed before generating the world"
- Navigation intact: sidebar links (Launchpad, New Campaign, Library, Settings) all functional
- User can go back to concept and retry

### Attempt 2/3
- Action: Cleared session, re-filled concept, Continue to DNA
- Result: FAILED in ~3 seconds
- Visible UI: Same as attempt 1 -- empty DNA with validation message
- Recovery state: Same recoverable state, buttons and navigation intact
- Flow data preserved on concept page (name, premise, franchise) after going back

### Attempt 3/3
- Action: Cleared session, re-filled concept, Continue to DNA
- Result: FAILED in ~12 seconds
- Visible UI: Same error pattern -- empty DNA, validation message
- Final failure reporting: Toast notification "Failed to generate suggestions" with description
- No silent spinner or dead state after 3rd failure
- UI remains fully navigable with clear recovery paths

## Post-3rd-Failure UI Assessment
After 3 consecutive failures:
- Page is NOT dead-ended or stuck
- Navigation sidebar remains fully functional
- User can go back to concept page (data preserved)
- User can try "Start With Manual DNA" to bypass LLM suggestions
- Validation message clearly states what's needed
- No corruption of flow state or session data

## Recovery After Restoring Valid Settings
- Restored original GLM API key via POST /api/settings
- Cleared session, re-filled concept, clicked Continue to DNA
- DNA suggestions completed successfully after ~250 seconds (GLM-5.1 sequential calls)
- All 6 DNA categories populated with real content
- Flow fully operational after settings fix

## Automated Test Results
- page.test.tsx (concept): 3/3 passed
- page.test.tsx (DNA): 3/3 passed
- flow-provider.test.tsx: 1/1 passed

## Assessment
The D-06 retry protocol is operationally sound:
- Each failure attempt leaves the UI in a recoverable state
- Flow data (name, premise) persists across retries
- Error feedback is provided via toast notifications (transient but visible)
- After restoring valid settings, the same step succeeds with real LLM calls
- No cumulative retry counter in the UI (each attempt is independent)
- The UI never stalls silently or dead-ends after any number of failures
